{"id":"c2m-hua","title":"Add Rust crate coverage to CI pipeline","description":"## Problem\n\nThe CI `ci:test:unit` task only measures Python coverage via pytest-cov. The Rust\n`csafe-codec` crate has its own test suite (passes in \"Rust Checks\" job) but coverage\nis not collected or reported. The Python coverage gate (`--fail-under=80`) fails with\n0% because the Python tests exercise Rust FFI bindings, not Python source.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. Add a Taskfile task (e.g. `ci:test:rust-coverage`) that runs `cargo llvm-cov` for\n   `csafe-codec` and outputs lcov/xml coverage.\n2. Update the CI workflow to collect Rust coverage and upload it to Codecov alongside\n   Python coverage (separate flags/components).\n3. Fix the Python `ci:test:unit` task so it does not fail when there is no Python\n   source to measure (either skip the gate or adjust `--fail-under` dynamically).\n4. Add `CODECOV_TOKEN` repo secret (manual step, documented).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- `task ci:test:unit` passes when no Python source is covered.\n- Rust test coverage is visible in Codecov under a separate flag.\n- CI green on both Python-only and Rust-only PRs.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"mail@fabiankoerner.com","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:32:16Z","created_by":"Fabian Koerner","updated_at":"2026-04-18T07:33:46Z","closed_at":"2026-03-24T06:36:29Z","close_reason":"Implemented cargo-llvm-cov coverage pipeline with Codecov flags","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
